ZH: 他丢下了工作不想做。
EN: He abandoned the work and didn't want to do it.

ZH: 她丢下了家里的一切去旅行。
EN: She left everything at home to travel.

ZH: 孩子们丢下玩具去追逐彩虹。
EN: The children left their toys and chased after the rainbow.

ZH: 我不得不丢下原计划去参加急需的会议。
EN: I had to abandon my original plan to attend the urgent meeting.

ZH: 他丢下繁忙的工作抽出时间陪伴家人。
EN: He left his busy work to spend time with his family.

ZH: 她丢下衣服在地上。
EN: She dropped her clothes on the floor.

ZH: 我丢下书包直接出门了。
EN: I left my backpack and went out directly.

ZH: 他们丢下问题没有解决。
EN: They left the issue unresolved.

ZH: 小狗丢下了它的玩具去迎接主人。
EN: The puppy abandoned its toy to greet its owner.

ZH: 他们丢下一切参加了义工活动。
EN: They abandoned everything to participate in volunteer activities.

ZH: 她丢下了伞在车上。
EN: She left her umbrella in the car.

ZH: 骑手丢下马匹帮助伤的人。
EN: The rider abandoned the horse to help the injured.

ZH: 我们不能丢下这个机会。
EN: We cannot miss this opportunity.

ZH: 快点，不要丢下我们！
EN: Hurry up, don't leave us behind!

ZH: 她丢下了咖啡杯在咖啡厅里。
EN: She dropped her coffee cup in the coffee shop.

ZH: 他丢下家庭问题直接去上班。
EN: He left behind family problems and went to work directly.

ZH: 学生们丢下教材插好书签。
EN: The students left their textbooks with bookmarks.

ZH: 我们不能丢下爱护环境的责任。
EN: We cannot neglect our responsibility to protect the environment.

ZH: 警察丢下吃饭的机会追捕罪犯。
EN: The police abandoned the chance to eat to pursue the criminal.

ZH: 让我们丢下不愉快的过去，向新的未来出发。
EN: Let's leave behind the unhappy past and move towards a new future.
